description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a motivated and skilled Occupational Therapist to become part of an innovative Paediatric Occupational Therapy team. We work across the health board, working closely with our stakeholders, which include education, health and third sectors. The successful candidate will have experience of working with children and young people and their support networks. We are looking for an OT that is enthusiastic, flexible and committed to developing themselves and service delivery. The post is based in Hafan Y Mor Childrens Centre, which has excellent facilities. The post often requires working in schools, community facilities and families homes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
